        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 12:27PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1227 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Stinnett, or 14 miles northeast of Borger, moving east
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Hutchinson and central Roberts Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
